HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!! CHANCE 11 WILL TAKE 11 CHANCES FOR YOU TO FINALLY GET A POSITIVE EXPERIENCE. Came here on a Saturday for food and drinks with my friends. We sat ourselves and waited quite a while for someone to take our orders (no one ever came). FInally, we asked the bouncer, how do we place an order? We were advised to go to the bar because they were short staffed that night. (I shouldn't have to tell you how inconvenient it would be to have to walk back and forth through a crowded to get our own food and drinks).  Soon after, a man appeared at our table asking what we wanted. Just like that! No greeting, apology or acknowledgement of his delay. He was combative and unhelpful when I had questions about the menu. 40 minutes later, my friends and I grew impatient waiting for at least our drinks. One of my friends approached the bar to ask for a manager, a security guard stepped in and asked what she wanted, she repeated, A MANAGER. The security guard nodded and directed her to the owner THE RUDE MAN THAT TOOK OUR ORDERS.  She told him how we had waited 40 minutes and had not received our food or drinks. He said the kitchen was backed up and our food would be out in about 20 minutes. Naturally, she asked why no one had notified us of this delay, to which he replied WELL I'M TELLING YOU NOW. (keep in mind we ordered burgers and shrimp entrees, 10-15 min tops!) And you might be wondering, well what about our drinks? She asked about those and was told there were almost ready. ALMOST ready!!! Every group there was experiencing the same thing! No drinks, unless they got up and went to the bar, and no food AT ALL.  The owner offered to comp our drinks, but that wasn't going to cut, we left and went next door to the diner where they were friendly and quick with our meals. I guess it might really take 11 chances to get good service or any service in this place.
